{
  "id": "11",
  "name": "Imputing With Mode Value",
  "description": "Imputing with most frequently observed value. It fills missing values (None) in selected columns with most frequently observed value in the corresponding column, in the incoming DataFrame.",
  "type": "transform",
  "nodeClass": "fire.nodes.ml.NodeReplaceMissingValueWithMode",
  "engine":"all",
  "fields" : [
    {"name":"colNames", "value":"[]", "widget": "variables", "title": "Columns", "description": "Columns to be processed for imputing the missing values.",  "datatypes":["string","integer","double","float", "long"]}
  ]
}

start-details:

This node imputes the missing values in the specified columns by mode of the values in the column.

end-details:

start-examples:

Incoming Dataframe has following rows and [AGE] column has missing value / [NULL] for some rows:

CUST_CD    |    CUST_NAME    |    AGE
------------------------------------------
C01        |    MATT         |    50
C02        |    LISA         |    45
C03        |    ROBIN        |	
C04        |    MARCUS       |	
C05        |    MARK         |    30
C06        |    DAVID        |    30
C07        |    ANTHONY      |    90

If imputingwithmodevalue node is configured to Impute [AGE] with mode value then missing values in [AGE] column would be replaced with 30 which is the mode of [AGE] column.
Outgoing Dataframe would result as below:

CUST_CD    |    CUST_NAME    |    AGE
------------------------------------------
C01        |    MATT         |    50
C02        |    LISA         |    45
C03        |    ROBIN        |    30	
C04        |    MARCUS       |    30	
C05        |    MARK         |    30
C06        |    DAVID        |    30
C07        |    ANTHONY      |    90


end-examples:

